It&#8217;s not yet clear what residents are protesting about but motorists have been warned to avoid the area. JOHANNESBURG A protest is underway in Freedom Park south of Johannesburg on Monday morning, with residents blocking the N12 and Golden highways.It s not yet clear what residents are protesting about but motorists have been warned to avoid the area.The Johannesburg Metro Police Department s Wayne Minnaar says more officers are being deployed. There are still some vehicles making U-turns on the freeway, so motorists are urged to drive with caution. More to follow.